race.comment: PERFECTLY PROPER (8) was scratched in October due to a floating mishap and reappeared with a nice trial at Belmont recently. Her 2YO form was very impressive and she looks in similar order coming into this. Likely to get back from the draw, but can finish over the top of her rivals. CALL ME FROSTY (3) sat on the speed at Ascot and finished 1.9L off the winner last start when jumping favourite in Saturday grade. Back to maiden company now and Nottle's claim comes in handy. He maps to be prominent in the run once again and a forward showing is on the cards. TAWAAJ (12) is on debut today and has shown positive signs at the trials coming into this. Her latest outing under Whittington was one of her best and this looks a race where she can be in the finish. MOJO MIO (5) was just fair on debut but has trialled well coming into this. Can return on a positive note.
